CatDescriptText: Beautiful backyard landscape of Mr. Ira. F. Lewis, president of Pittsburgh Courier newspaper. His home still stands on the 600 block of Wilkinsburg Avenue at the top of one of Pittsburgh's steepest hills.  His garden and yard was used to entertain the Pittsburgh elite and for the marriage of Mr. Lewis's daughter.  Lewis began work at the Courier in 1914, and died 1948.
TitMainTitle: Backyard garden with brick steps, lawn furniture on left, and square patterned lattice, at residence of Ira Lewis, 616 Wilkinsburg Avenue, Homewood, horizontal format
